      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Michael Parker became the first Non-Executive Chairman of the Maritime & Coastguard Agency in January 2017.</p>

<p>Prior to this appointment, Michael was the Chairman of the UK holding company of CMA CGM and its UK subsidiary MacAndrews & Co Ltd.</p>

<p>Michael commenced his shipping career in 1970 with Overseas Container Ltd. In 1984, he joined Ellerman Lines and was part of the team that led the management buy-out in 1985. From 1991 to 2009 Michael Parker was first Managing Director and then Chairman of Andrew Weir Shipping Ltd. In 2004/2005 he was President of the Chamber of Shipping and has represented the UK Chamber at both the European Shipownersâ€™ Association and the International Chamber of Shipping.</p>
</div>
      </section>

